> Hello everyone,
>
> I have a three part question about a 78 Westy (FI) I
> am restoring.
>
> First, I noticed the brown wire going into the voltage
> regulator has had its insulation melted off, has
> anyone had a similar problem and if so, what are the
> likely causes?

If the engine is not grounded to the frame with a heavy ground cable (same
guage as battery ground cable ) , the brown wire takes all the current,
which is to much for that size wire, espesially if you keep spinning the
starter over and over trying to start it.

Joey.



